## Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Required"
description: "Recommended for SEO"
sidebarTitle: "Optional — shorter sidebar label"
---
```

Do not add `id`, `blueprint`, `updated_at`, `landing`, or `nav_title`.

## Mintlify MDX components (callout syntax)

```mdx
<Note>Informational.</Note>
<Info>Supplementary context.</Info>
<Tip>Best practice.</Tip>
<Warning>Destructive action warning.</Warning>
<Frame><img src="/images/..." alt="..." /></Frame>
```

Never use Markdoc (`{% callout %}`), old Docusaurus (`:::note`), or raw HTML divs for callouts.

## Writing style (summary — see CLAUDE.md for full rules)

- Active voice — "Statsig processes data" not "data is processed" (two passes required)
- Present tense — remove `will`, `will be`, `going to`
- Contractions always — `can't`, `doesn't`, `won't`
- No "please" in instructions
- Replace `in order to` → `to`, `prior to` → `before`, `utilize` → `use`, `via` → `through`
- "See [doc]" → "Go to [doc]" (accessibility rule)
- No `we`/`our`/`us` — use "Statsig" or "you"
- **Bold** for interactive UI elements, *Italics* for nav paths
- List items end with a period
- Sentence-case headings, no end punctuation, body starts at `##`

